Cornelis Bernardus &quot;Kees&quot; Bastiaans (20 November 1909, Mill, Netherlands - 31 March 1986, Mill) was a Dutch Painter. He was an Expressionist, often with a religious theme to his work. One of his paintings Familieportret is exhibited in the Noordbrabants Museum in 's-Hertogenbosch.
For examples of his prolific work, and further information (in Dutch), visit the official web-site.1
